definitions.definition: A means of indemnity against a future occurrence of an uncertain event.
examples: The car was totalled, but fortunately I had insurance .
After five years in banking, I switched to insurance .

definitions.definition: Any attempt to forestall an unfavorable event .
examples: The sky was clear, but I took my umbrella for insurance .

definitions.definition: A bet made after the deal, which pays off if the dealer has blackjack .
examples: I only take insurance if the count is right.

main_definition: A means of indemnity against a future occurrence of an uncertain event.
secondary_definitions: ( figurative ) Any attempt to forestall an unfavorable event .
( blackjack ) A bet made after the deal, which pays off if the dealer has blackjack .
